3
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:47,767
- LATTE AND MOCHA.
- THANK YOU.

4
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:49,500
Woman:
 <i>THANKS.</i>

5
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,434
 <i>( printer whirring )</i>

6
00:01:57,167 --> 00:02:00,167
- Man: <i>VINCENT'S MERGER'S DEAD.</i>
- Woman: <i>DON'T WORRY</i>
ABOUT IT, L.

7
00:02:00,167 --> 00:02:02,001
 <i>YOU'LL BE OUT OF HERE</i>
 <i>IN SIX MONTHS.</i>

8
00:02:02,001 --> 00:02:03,767
THE "UNTIL" JOB.

9
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:09,001
HOW LONG YOU BEEN
WORKING HERE, BEN?

10
00:02:09,001 --> 00:02:10,834
EIGHT YEARS.

11
00:02:10,834 --> 00:02:13,001
Woman: <i>JESUS.</i>

12
00:02:13,001 --> 00:02:14,967
I KNOW.
PRETTY PATHETIC.

13
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:18,234
AT LEAST I DON'T DELUDE MYSELF
WITH HOPES AND DREAMS.

14
00:02:18,234 --> 00:02:19,834
HE'S AGAINST
HOPES AND DREAMS.

15
00:02:19,834 --> 00:02:21,600
HE'S THE ANTI-EVERYTHING
DUDE.

16
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,600
THE ANTICHRIST.

17
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:27,001
YOU THINK GETTING A JOB
IN A TV SERIES IS GOING
TO CHANGE ANYTHING?

18
00:02:27,001 --> 00:02:29,900
IN THREE DAYS,
YOU'LL REALIZE IT'S
JUST THE SAME OLD CRAP

19
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:33,734
IN A NEW PACKAGE--
YOU'LL STILL BE WORKING
FOR THE MAN,

20
00:02:33,734 --> 00:02:35,734
SAME AS EVERYONE ELSE.

21
00:02:35,734 --> 00:02:38,167
Woman:
 <i>THE MAN?</i>
 <i>WHO'S THE MAN?</i>

22
00:02:38,167 --> 00:02:41,700
L:
 <i>YOU KNOW-- SOCIETY,</i>
 <i>THE ESTABLISHMENT,</i>

23
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,633
 <i>THE CORPORATE</i>
 <i>SUPER-ORGANISM.</i>

24
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:45,567
- <i>( all laughing )</i>
- Woman: <i>OH, HIM.</i>

25
00:02:45,567 --> 00:02:48,401
YOU'RE ONE DARK DUDE, MAN.

26
00:02:51,468 --> 00:02:54,134
( knocks )

27
00:02:54,134 --> 00:02:56,667
- <i>( sports on TV )</i>
- HE'S HERE.

28
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:06,867
HI, DAD.

29
00:03:09,934 --> 00:03:12,267
SO WHAT'S NEW
IN SCHOOL?

30
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:14,067
I DON'T KNOW.

31
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:16,401
MATH AND STUFF.

32
00:03:16,401 --> 00:03:20,201
 <i>A GURU FROM AN ASHRAM</i>
 <i>IN INDIA CAME TO VISIT US</i>

33
00:03:20,201 --> 00:03:22,734
 <i>IN SOCIAL STUDIES.</i>

34
00:03:22,734 --> 00:03:25,633
HE COULD REMEMBER
TWO OF HIS PAST LIVES.

35
00:03:27,034 --> 00:03:29,101
 <i>THAT KID RECOGNIZES YOU.</i>

36
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:34,267
PROBABLY FROM ONE
OF YOUR C.D.s.

37
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:36,301
WHAT WERE
HIS PAST LIVES?

38
00:03:36,301 --> 00:03:38,934
IN ONE
HE WAS A PRINCE.

39
00:03:38,934 --> 00:03:42,700
IN THE OTHER
HE WAS A SLAVE
LEADING A REBELLION.

40
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,900
THAT'S THE TROUBLE
WITH REINCARNATION--

41
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,201
EVERYBODY WAS ALWAYS
A PRINCE OR A WARRIOR.

42
00:03:47,201 --> 00:03:49,401
 <i>NOBODY WAS EVER</i>
 <i>A MUSEUM GUARD,</i>

43
00:03:49,401 --> 00:03:52,034
A PARAMECIUM
OR A BED OF MOSS.

44
00:03:52,034 --> 00:03:55,567
PEOPLE WANT TO THINK
THEY WERE SPECIAL, I GUESS.

45
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:57,468
 <i>YEAH, WELL,</i>
 <i>THAT'S HOW THEY GET YOU.</i>

46
00:03:57,468 --> 00:04:00,401
THEY FIGURE IF THEY CAN
FILL YOU UP WITH THAT
PIE-IN-THE-SKY STUFF,

47
00:04:00,401 --> 00:04:02,867
MAYBE YOU WON'T NOTICE
HOW MUCH CRAP YOU'VE EATEN
IN YOUR OWN LIFETIME.

48
00:04:04,734 --> 00:04:06,533
READY?

49
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:10,600
I THINK
I'M A LESBIAN.

50
00:04:14,401 --> 00:04:17,101
WHY, 'CAUSE YOU
LIKE HOCKEY?

51
00:04:17,101 --> 00:04:19,167
I LIKE BOYS, BUT...

52
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:22,067
NOT TO KISS. I LIKE
HANGING OUT WITH THEM.

53
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:25,434
OH. I WOULDN'T JUMP
TO ANY CONCLUSIONS.

54
00:04:25,434 --> 00:04:28,067
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN REACHED
PUBERTY YET.

55
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,967
YOU'RE PROGRAMMED
FROM BIRTH.

56
00:04:29,967 --> 00:04:31,867
THEY HAVE STUDIES.

57
00:04:35,301 --> 00:04:38,101
SO...

58
00:04:38,101 --> 00:04:40,934
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?
YOU WANNA GO ICE SKATING?

59
00:04:40,934 --> 00:04:43,334
DAD, I LIKE
WATCHING HOCKEY.

60
00:04:43,334 --> 00:04:46,267
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW TO SKATE.

61
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:49,334
DO YOU WANT TO GO
TO McRORY'S?

62
00:04:49,334 --> 00:04:51,134
 <i>SURE.</i>

63
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,468
Man:
 <i>VERY GOOD.</i>
 <i>NICE-- NICE GUITAR.</i>

64
00:05:01,468 --> 00:05:04,034
- Ben: <i>MM-HMM.</i>
- HEY, BEN, THIS JUST CAME IN.

65
00:05:04,034 --> 00:05:05,967
BRAZILIAN.

66
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:08,368
SO FINE IT ALMOST
PLAYS ITSELF.

67
00:05:08,368 --> 00:05:11,600
( strumming )

68
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,533
YOU WANT TO PLAY IT?
GO AHEAD.

69
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:16,167
JIM AND SWEENY ARE
IN THE BACK.

70
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:19,167
DO YOU MIND?
JUST FOR A MINUTE?

71
00:05:22,834 --> 00:05:25,468
- ( strumming )
- MAESTRO!

72
00:05:25,468 --> 00:05:28,500
ALL RIGHT. I SEE
YOU GOT THE BRAZILIAN.

73
00:06:04,001 --> 00:06:06,034
SWEET.

74
00:06:06,034 --> 00:06:08,500
IT'S A SHAME.

75
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,034
WHAT IS?

76
00:06:10,034 --> 00:06:13,001
TO BE SO GREAT AT SOMETHING
NO ONE CARES ABOUT.

77
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:34,301
I THINK I WANT TO SLEEP
IN MY OWN ROOM TONIGHT.

78
00:06:35,468 --> 00:06:37,600
IBOU SNORES TOO LOUD

79
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:41,600
AND I HAVE
A BIO QUIZ TOMORROW.

80
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,633
OH.

81
00:06:45,234 --> 00:06:46,867
HEY, WHAT'S THE MATTER?

82
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:49,800
SHE WANTED TO COME HOME,
THAT'S ALL.

83
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,934
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

84
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:55,368
HEY, SWEETIE.

85
00:06:55,368 --> 00:06:58,867
WHAT DID YOU SAY TO HER?
FOR GOD'S SAKES, BEN,

86
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:02,500
SHE'S 11 YEARS OLD.
SHE STILL WANTS TO THINK
THE WORLD IS A NICE PLACE.

87
00:07:07,734 --> 00:07:09,434
HEY.

88
00:07:09,434 --> 00:07:12,567
SHE WANTS ME TO FEED HER 
THAT POSITIVE-THINK CRAP.

89
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:17,034
WE JUST EXITED THE BLOODIEST
CENTURY IN THE HISTORY
OF CIVILIZATION.

90
00:07:17,034 --> 00:07:21,234
WE GOT TERRORISM,
ATOMIC BOMBS,

91
00:07:21,234 --> 00:07:24,401
GENOCIDE OF
MYTHIC PROPORTIONS.

92
00:07:24,401 --> 00:07:26,767
AND WHAT HAVE ALL
THESE HORRORS PRODUCED

93
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:28,767
AS WE GO INTO
THE NEW MILLENNIUM?

94
00:07:28,767 --> 00:07:31,234
POSITIVE FUCKING THINKING.

95
00:07:31,234 --> 00:07:32,734
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT'S ABOUT?

96
00:07:32,734 --> 00:07:34,934
IT'S ABOUT GRABBING
AS MUCH AS YOU CAN 

97
00:07:34,934 --> 00:07:37,067
WITH YOUR GREEDY
LITTLE FINGERS.

98
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:40,034
SO WHY DON'T YOU DO
SOMETHING SPECIAL WITH HER?

99
00:07:40,034 --> 00:07:42,201
TAKE HER TO A HOCKEY GAME
OR SOMETHING.

100
00:07:42,201 --> 00:07:46,934
THE ONLY CRIME LEFT IN
THE WHOLE FUCKING WORLD
IS NEGATIVITY.

101
00:07:46,934 --> 00:07:49,034
NEGATIVITY IS TREASON.

102
00:07:49,034 --> 00:07:51,700
THEY EVEN HAVE
A PILL FOR IT.

103
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:55,434
IT IS A WORLD IN WHICH
THE MAN IS THE PRESIDING
AUTHORITY, HUH?

104
00:07:55,434 --> 00:07:58,734
THE TWO WORST INVENTIONS
IN THE PAST 20 YEARS--

105
00:07:58,734 --> 00:08:01,368
THE TV REMOTE
AND POSITIVE THINKING.

106
00:08:03,434 --> 00:08:07,633
YOU KNOW, I-- I HEAR
SOMETHING ON THE RADIO TODAY.

107
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:10,067
IT WAS VERY INTERESTING.

108
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:12,900
IT WAS ABOUT
THIS GAME THEORY.

109
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,934
THEY SAY IF A MAN ACTS
IN HIS OWN INTERESTS,

110
00:08:15,934 --> 00:08:19,667
THAT HE WOULD ACT IN A WAY
THAT IS BENEFICIAL TO
THOSE AROUND HIM--

111
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:21,967
IF HE ACTS INTELLIGENTLY.

112
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:23,468
BIG "IF."

113
00:08:23,468 --> 00:08:26,301
( laughs )

114
00:08:26,301 --> 00:08:29,001
I DON'T KNOW.
SO I WENT ON THE INTERNET

115
00:08:29,001 --> 00:08:31,301
TO READ A LITTLE MORE
ABOUT IT, YOU KNOW?

116
00:08:31,301 --> 00:08:33,734
AND THE CAKE IS--

117
00:08:33,734 --> 00:08:36,001
HOW YOU SAY?
--MUTUAL GAME THEORY.

118
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:39,867
THEY SAY, YOU KNOW,

119
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:42,468
THE GAME THEORY BETWEEN
TWO FRIENDS,

120
00:08:42,468 --> 00:08:46,134
LIKE EACH ONE WANTING
WHAT IS BEST FOR THE OTHER.

121
00:08:46,134 --> 00:08:48,301
MMM.

122
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:57,201
NO FRET, NO FRET.
GLUCOSE SPIKE, YEAH?

123
00:08:57,201 --> 00:09:00,600
( grunts )

124
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:03,301
LIKE YOU ARE
MY FRIEND, RIGHT?

125
00:09:03,301 --> 00:09:06,201
SO THAT WHICH YOU WANT,
I WANT FOR YOU.

126
00:09:06,201 --> 00:09:09,567
I GO OUT OF MY WAY
FOR YOU, BEN.

127
00:09:09,567 --> 00:09:12,167
I WOULD DO IT HAPPILY
BECAUSE I KNOW

128
00:09:12,167 --> 00:09:16,001
YOU WOULD DO THE SAME.

129
00:09:16,001 --> 00:09:19,401
GREAT THINGS CAN COME
FROM THIS GAME THEORY--

130
00:09:19,401 --> 00:09:21,533
 <i>GREAT THINGS.</i>

131
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:24,834
 <i>YOU KNOW,</i>
 <i>THE WOLOFS BACK</i>
 <i>IN SENEGAL,</i>

132
00:09:24,834 --> 00:09:28,900
WE DON'T SAY,
"THAT MAN HAS THIS"

133
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,633
OR "THIS MAN HAS THAT."

134
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:34,834
THAT IS WHY STILL MAGIC 
EXISTS IN SENEGAL, YEAH?

135
00:09:34,834 --> 00:09:36,834
WHAT KIND OF MAGIC IS THAT?

136
00:09:36,834 --> 00:09:39,900
WHEN IT RAINS, THE FISH,

137
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:42,334
THEY FALL FROM THE SKY.

138
00:09:42,334 --> 00:09:44,600
 <i>THIS HAPPENS</i>
 <i>BECAUSE WE BELIEVE.</i>

139
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:48,633
IT IS LIKE-- LIKE A FORM
OF GAME THEORY, I THINK.

140
00:09:51,034 --> 00:09:53,201
THERE'S AN OLD WOLOF SAYING:

141
00:09:53,201 --> 00:09:55,600
( speaks Wolof )

142
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,201
"YOUR THOUGHTS ARE THINGS."

143
00:09:58,201 --> 00:10:00,401
 <i>AND YOU'VE SEEN THIS?</i>

144
00:10:00,401 --> 00:10:02,434
YOU'VE SEEN FISH
FALL FROM THE SKY?

145
00:10:02,434 --> 00:10:04,867
WITH MY OWN EYES.

146
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:07,167
THE FISH, THEY FLAP
ABOUT IN THE GRASS,

147
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:09,567
TRYING TO GET BACK
IN THE STREAM.

148
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:12,834
I TOLD MY SISTER
ABOUT IT IN A LETTER.

149
00:10:15,101 --> 00:10:17,633
SHE HAS SEEN IT TOO,
YOU KNOW.

150
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:25,867
CHECK MATE.

151
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:33,267
EVERY TIME WE PLAY,
YOU GET ME INTO ONE
OF THESE CONVERSATIONS.

152
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:35,533
IT'S A GODDAMN DECOY.

153
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:38,301
MAYBE YOU SHOULD LOOK AT
THE WORLD AS YOUR FRIEND.

154
00:10:38,301 --> 00:10:40,401
YEAH,

155
00:10:40,401 --> 00:10:42,734
AS SOON AS I SEE FISH
FALL FROM THE SKY.

156
00:10:46,734 --> 00:10:49,201
YOUR--

157
00:10:49,201 --> 00:10:52,067
YOUR CAR IS SUPPOSED TO BE
FLUSH WITH THE POLE.

158
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:54,134
THIS HAS BEEN GOING ON
SINCE I MOVED IN.

159
00:10:54,134 --> 00:10:56,167
IT TAKES ME FIVE SWINGS
TO GET OUT OF MY SPOT.

160
00:10:56,167 --> 00:10:59,101
WHAT DO YOU DO?
COME OUT HERE WITH A RULER?

161
00:10:59,101 --> 00:11:01,334
BOTTOM LINE--
YOUR CAR IS ILLEGAL.

162
00:11:01,334 --> 00:11:04,800
 <i>I'M TRYING TO BE CIVIL</i>
 <i>ABOUT THIS, DUDE, YOU KNOW?</i>

163
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,001
 <i>I COULD JUST CALL THE POLICE</i>
 <i>AND HAVE YOUR CAR TOWED.</i>

164
00:11:07,001 --> 00:11:09,800
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE?
YOU'RE A VAMPIRE.

165
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,633
YOU THINK YOU'RE
NEW TO THE EARTH,
BUT YOU'RE NOT.

166
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:13,667
YOU'VE BEEN AROUND FOR,
LIKE, 10,000 YEARS.

167
00:11:13,667 --> 00:11:16,468
YOU WERE IN THE BIBLE.
YOU'RE INDESTRUCTIBLE.

168
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:18,600
YOU'RE LIKE AN INSECT.

169
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,567
AND WHEN THE NUCLEAR
HOLOCAUST COMES,

170
00:11:20,567 --> 00:11:23,134
THERE'LL BE SWARMS OF YOU
DRIVING AROUND IN YOUR S.U.V.s

171
00:11:23,134 --> 00:11:25,934
- INFORMING ON EACH OTHER.
- PARK WHERE IT'S LEGAL!

172
00:11:25,934 --> 00:11:27,767
SHUT UP.

173
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:36,800
SO 8:30, FRIDAY,
FUNNY BONE.

174
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:40,101
EVERYONE'S COMING, RIGHT?
CASSIE? LEON?

175
00:11:40,101 --> 00:11:41,867
- CASSIE?
- YES.

176
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:43,800
OKAY. CLAIRE?

177
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,934
 <i>FUNNY BONE, FRIDAY?</i>
 <i>YOU GOTTA COME.</i>

178
00:11:45,934 --> 00:11:49,867
 <i>I REP A COMIC AND HE'S</i>
 <i>GONNA BE ON AT 10:00, SO...</i>

179
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:57,500
( snoring )

180
00:12:41,567 --> 00:12:43,900
WHO ARE YOU?

181
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:46,700
I'M THE MAN.

182
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,667
ARE YOU GOD?

183
00:12:49,667 --> 00:12:53,001
NO, HE DEALS WITH
THE BIRDS AND BEASTIES,

184
00:12:53,001 --> 00:12:55,401
PLANETARY ALIGNMENTS,
QUARKS.

185
00:12:55,401 --> 00:12:57,700
 <i>I JUST DEAL WITH</i>
 <i>THE HUMAN ELEMENT.</i>

186
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,900
THEN I HAVE 
A QUESTION--

187
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:04,267
WHY ARE THERE SODA MACHINES
IN SCHOOLS?

188
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:07,967
WHY IS IT ALL ABOUT
GREED, AGENDA, MONEY?

189
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:10,600
 <i>IT IS EASIER TO</i>
 <i>KEEP PEOPLE IN LINE</i>

190
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:13,934
BY APPEALING
TO THEIR WORST IMPULSES
THAN THEIR BEST.

191
00:13:13,934 --> 00:13:17,001
NOW EVERYONE HAS
BAD IMPULSES, MMM?

192
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,134
NOT EVERYONE HAS
GOOD ONES.

193
00:13:38,934 --> 00:13:42,567
MAXINE, GO GET DRESSED.
LUCAS, GO GET DRESSED
FOR SCHOOL.

194
00:13:42,567 --> 00:13:44,267
LUCAS?

195
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:47,134
THANK YOU.
GO GET DRESSED, SWEETIE.

196
00:13:47,134 --> 00:13:49,267
( laughs )

197
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:53,101
HEY. LOOK AT
THIS ASS CLOWN.

198
00:13:55,134 --> 00:13:58,001
- WHO IS THAT?
- IT'S A GUY I WORK WITH.

199
00:13:58,001 --> 00:14:00,034
- IN PROOFREADING?
- YEAH.

200
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:05,334
DID YOU KNOW THAT THERE'S
A NEW STUDY THAT SAYS

201
00:14:05,334 --> 00:14:07,500
CINNAMON IS GOOD
FOR THE HEART?

202
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:10,334
I'M NOT LISTENING.
YOU'RE JUST TRYING
TO GET ME OFF MY GAME.

203
00:14:10,334 --> 00:14:12,633
NO NO NO,
SERIOUSLY, THOUGH,

204
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:15,767
DARK CHOCOLATE LOWERS
THE BLOOD PRESSURE,

205
00:14:15,767 --> 00:14:17,767
- TANNINS IN RED WINE.
- <i>( phone ringing )</i>

206
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:21,368
ALL THE MEDICINE
WE'LL EVER NEED IS
IN THE FOOD.

207
00:14:21,368 --> 00:14:23,600
20 YEARS FROM NOW
YOU WILL HAVE CANCER--

208
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,434
THE DOCTOR WILL
MAKE YOU A SALAD.

209
00:14:26,434 --> 00:14:28,368
- <i>( beeps )</i>
- <i>Hey, Ben, Cyril G. here.</i>

210
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,834
 <i>I'm going down the list, </i>
 <i>and you're coming, right?</i>

211
00:14:30,834 --> 00:14:32,600
YOU GOT SOMEWHERE
TO GO, EH?

212
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,934
 <i>All right,</i>
 <i>I'll see you there!</i>

213
00:14:33,934 --> 00:14:35,767
HE JUST NEEDS
A WARM BODY.

214
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:38,533
( speaks Wolof )

215
00:14:41,101 --> 00:14:44,234
BUT OF COURSE,
THE CONSUMABLES HAVE
THEIR OWN PERILS--

216
00:14:44,234 --> 00:14:47,900
MERCURY IN THE FISH,
CAFFEINE.

217
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:51,567
MAYBE ONE FOOD WILL
CURE CANCER, YEAH?

