- I'LL SEE HER NEXT WEEKEND.

429
00:30:26,167 --> 00:30:28,434
UM, NO.

430
00:30:28,434 --> 00:30:31,667
ACTUALLY, YOU WON'T
BECAUSE WE HAVE THE SCHOOL
CAMPING TRIP, SO...

431
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:37,633
YOU WANT TO-- UM,
YOU WANT TO COME IN FOR A SEC?

432
00:30:37,633 --> 00:30:39,734
NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

433
00:30:39,734 --> 00:30:42,533
I'LL SEE YOU LATER, ELIZA.

434
00:31:01,934 --> 00:31:05,267
( machines beeping )

435
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:08,767
WHAT IS--
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

436
00:31:08,767 --> 00:31:10,633
HIS BLOOD PRESSURE
WENT DOWN.

437
00:31:10,633 --> 00:31:12,633
CAN WE CLEAR
THE ROOM, PLEASE?

438
00:31:12,633 --> 00:31:14,533
I WILL STAY HERE.

439
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,134
SO WHAT'S WITH
THE SNEAKERS?

440
00:31:28,134 --> 00:31:31,001
SNEAKERS?

441
00:31:31,001 --> 00:31:33,967
 <i>THE NIKES.</i>

442
00:31:33,967 --> 00:31:37,067
OH, YES.
THE NIKES.

443
00:31:37,067 --> 00:31:41,167
IT IS VERY HARD
TO GET NIKES

444
00:31:41,167 --> 00:31:44,533
IN OUR TINY
LITTLE SPOT

445
00:31:44,533 --> 00:31:46,734
 <i>ON THE GLOBE.</i>

446
00:31:49,667 --> 00:31:53,334
( speaks Wolof )

447
00:31:53,334 --> 00:31:56,633
IT IS A WOLOF EXPRESSION.

448
00:31:56,633 --> 00:32:00,934
"IF YOU DO NOT HAVE IT,
IT IS A TREASURE."

449
00:32:11,234 --> 00:32:15,434
NOW YOU TELL ME, PLEASE,
AMERICAN PHRASE.

450
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:18,368
OKAY.

451
00:32:19,867 --> 00:32:21,834
WELL...

452
00:32:21,834 --> 00:32:25,167
IN AMERICA,
WE HAVE A PHRASE,
"BOTTOM LINE."

453
00:32:25,167 --> 00:32:27,201
BOTTOM LINE?

454
00:32:27,201 --> 00:32:30,401
YEAH. YEAH, IT'S THE LINE
FROM AN ACCOUNTANT'S FORM 

455
00:32:30,401 --> 00:32:32,533
THAT TELLS YOU 
YOUR NET VALUE,

456
00:32:32,533 --> 00:32:35,234
BUT WE USE IT
WHEN WE'RE ABOUT
TO DO SOMETHING 

457
00:32:35,234 --> 00:32:37,633
THAT WE KNOW IS WRONG.
LIKE, WE'LL SAY,

458
00:32:37,633 --> 00:32:41,700
 <i>"BOTTOM LINE-- SHE ISN'T</i>
 <i>PRETTY ENOUGH," BEFORE</i>
 <i>WE DUMP A GIRLFRIEND</i>

459
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:43,700
OR, "BOTTOM LINE--
HE DOESN'T FIT INTO
THE COMPANY,"

460
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:45,434
BEFORE WE FIRE A GUY
WITH THREE KIDS.

461
00:32:45,434 --> 00:32:47,567
"BOTTOM LINE--

462
00:32:47,567 --> 00:32:50,101
HE DOES NOT FIT
INTO THE COMPANY."

463
00:32:50,101 --> 00:32:52,600
RIGHT. YOU UNDERSTAND
BOTTOM LINE,

464
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:55,234
YOU UNDERSTAND
AMERICA.

465
00:32:55,234 --> 00:32:59,734
IN DAKAR, WE ALL HAVE
EYE ON AMERICA.

466
00:32:59,734 --> 00:33:02,900
WE SEE IT ON TV, 
IN THE MAGAZINES.

467
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:06,434
IT IS TRULY
THE LAND OF MORE.

468
00:33:06,434 --> 00:33:10,267
SENEGAL IS A VERY
VERY SMALL COUNTRY.

469
00:33:10,267 --> 00:33:15,101
WE ALL ARE POOR,
EXCEPT A VERY VERY FEW.

470
00:33:15,101 --> 00:33:18,001
BOTTOM LINE.

471
00:33:24,734 --> 00:33:27,001
BACK TO HIS RUGGED SELF.

472
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:34,334
THAT DOCTOR IS...
( speaks Wolof ).

473
00:33:34,334 --> 00:33:36,633
HMM?

474
00:33:36,633 --> 00:33:39,533
ASSHOLE.
SHE IS ASSHOLE.

475
00:33:39,533 --> 00:33:41,834
SHE TREATS PEOPLE LIKE
THEY ARE WATER--

476
00:33:41,834 --> 00:33:43,967
ONE IS THE SAME
AS ANOTHER.

477
00:33:52,834 --> 00:33:54,633
- OH.
- EXCUSE ME.

478
00:34:18,167 --> 00:34:21,500
 <i>( man singing</i>
 <i>in Wolof )</i>

479
00:35:00,834 --> 00:35:05,301
I WILL-- I WILL BE
RETURNING HOME 
THIS AFTERNOON.

480
00:35:06,567 --> 00:35:08,368
BACK TO DAKAR?

481
00:35:08,368 --> 00:35:10,767
YES.

482
00:35:10,767 --> 00:35:13,500
I AM OUT OF FUNDS.

483
00:35:13,500 --> 00:35:15,834
WELL, YOU SPENT IT
ALL ON FOOTWEAR.

484
00:35:19,368 --> 00:35:22,967
THANK YOU FOR--
FOR EVERYTHING.

485
00:35:22,967 --> 00:35:27,001
WELL, IF IBOU--

486
00:35:28,301 --> 00:35:30,301
WHEN IBOU--
I'LL TELL HIM.

487
00:35:30,301 --> 00:35:33,734
YES, THANK YOU.

488
00:35:33,734 --> 00:35:35,800
YEAH.

489
00:36:06,434 --> 00:36:09,334
THIS IS FROM YOUR BROTHER'S
SAFETY DEPOSIT BOX.

490
00:36:09,334 --> 00:36:11,600
HE WOULD HAVE WANTED
YOU TO HAVE IT.

491
00:36:26,167 --> 00:36:28,434
- ( rings doorbell )
- PIEWORKS DELIVERY.

492
00:36:28,434 --> 00:36:31,633
OH, YEAH. CAN YOU HOLD ON
JUST ONE SEC, PLEASE?

493
00:36:31,633 --> 00:36:34,500
 <i>YEAH, NO, IT'S JUST THE TIMING</i>
 <i>IS REALLY TOUGH FOR ME.</i>

494
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:36,867
( girls laughing )

495
00:36:36,867 --> 00:36:38,800
GIRLS, NO RUNNING.

496
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:42,301
 <i>SO THAT'S ONE HALF MUSHROOMS,</i>
 <i>ONE HALF ANCHOVIES, RIGHT?</i>

497
00:36:45,934 --> 00:36:47,500
THANK YOU.

498
00:36:47,500 --> 00:36:50,067
THANK YOU.

499
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:09,434
 <i>( car alarm sounding )</i>

500
00:38:10,434 --> 00:38:12,401
 <i>( engine starts )</i>

501
00:38:54,468 --> 00:38:58,134
Khadi:
 <i>THERE MUST BE NO LIGHT</i>
 <i>EXCEPT FOR THE VOTIVE CANDLES.</i>

502
00:38:58,134 --> 00:39:01,734
IT IS...
( speaks Wolof ),

503
00:39:01,734 --> 00:39:05,867
WOLOF RITUAL,
TO MAKE HIM GET BETTER.

504
00:39:13,167 --> 00:39:15,667
YOU HELP, NO?

505
00:39:15,667 --> 00:39:19,201
OH. NO, I'LL PASS.
THANKS.

506
00:39:19,201 --> 00:39:21,533
COME HERE, BEN.

507
00:39:21,533 --> 00:39:24,134
SERIOUSLY,
YOU DON'T WANT ME.

508
00:39:24,134 --> 00:39:26,301
I'LL SEND BAD VIBES
OR SOMETHING.

509
00:39:26,301 --> 00:39:29,533
PLEASE,
IT IS BETTER WITH TWO.

510
00:39:32,134 --> 00:39:36,967
IN WOLOF, WE HAVE SAYING:
( speaks Wolof )

511
00:39:36,967 --> 00:39:39,600
"THOUGHTS ARE THINGS."

512
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:42,767
THIS SUBSTANCE
IS MY BROTHER 

513
00:39:42,767 --> 00:39:45,567
WHO WE ARE LONGING
TO GET BETTER.

514
00:39:48,334 --> 00:39:51,633
WE ASK HIS ANCESTORS
WHO ARE HERE

515
00:39:51,633 --> 00:39:54,401
TO THINK THESE SAME
HEALING THOUGHTS.

516
00:39:55,867 --> 00:39:59,067
IT HAS NO WEIGHT,
A THOUGHT-- NO CHARGE,

517
00:39:59,067 --> 00:40:03,700
NO PROPERTIES.
THOUGHTS DO NOT EXIST,

518
00:40:03,700 --> 00:40:05,967
NOT THE WAY
A CHAIR EXISTS.

519
00:40:05,967 --> 00:40:10,800
THEY CANNOT DIE.
WE BELIEVE IN THE POWER
OF OUR ANCESTORS

520
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:15,500
BECAUSE WE BELIEVE
THEIR THOUGHTS AND
FEELINGS ARE FOREVER.

521
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:22,201
IT IS SALT WATER
FROM THE OCEAN.

522
00:40:27,368 --> 00:40:31,234
IT IS NOW
A QUIET WAVE...

523
00:40:31,234 --> 00:40:33,468
LIKE HIM.

524
00:40:35,201 --> 00:40:38,001
MOVE YOUR FINGERS
THROUGH THE WATER.

525
00:40:40,401 --> 00:40:44,533
DO IT LIKE IT IS
A LIVING THING.

526
00:40:44,533 --> 00:40:46,500
BUT IT'S--
IT'S SEA WATER.

527
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:49,001
YOU DO NOT BELIEVE
IN MAGIC, NO?

528
00:40:51,201 --> 00:40:54,434
BUT MAGIC IS EVERYWHERE.

529
00:40:54,434 --> 00:40:56,900
FEELINGS ARE
MAGIC, NO?

530
00:40:56,900 --> 00:40:59,800
THE FEELINGS
PEOPLE HAVE;

531
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:03,700
WHAT A FEELING CAN DO
TO ANOTHER PERSON--

532
00:41:03,700 --> 00:41:07,633
IT IS LIKE
CHEMICAL REACTION.

533
00:41:07,633 --> 00:41:11,368
PUT YOUR EYES HERE.

534
00:41:11,368 --> 00:41:13,468
WE BOTH LOVE HIM.

535
00:41:13,468 --> 00:41:15,867
LET THE FEELINGS TALK.

536
00:41:28,001 --> 00:41:30,734
WAIT. PLEASE.

537
00:41:32,734 --> 00:41:36,301
WE LEAVE NOW.
YOU MUST NOT LOOK BEHIND.

538
00:41:36,301 --> 00:41:38,401
IF YOU LOOK BEHIND,
HE WILL NOT GET BETTER.

539
00:41:45,234 --> 00:41:47,500
I'M SORRY.

540
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:50,201
I DON'T KNOW WHY I--

541
00:42:26,201 --> 00:42:29,167
HMM.
MY FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL.

542
00:42:29,167 --> 00:42:31,468
IBOU WALKED ME.

543
00:42:31,468 --> 00:42:36,334
HE ALWAYS HELD A BIG STICK
TO PROTECT ME FROM SNAKES.

544
00:42:36,334 --> 00:42:39,001
I WAS NOT AFRAID
OF SNAKES,

545
00:42:39,001 --> 00:42:41,533
BUT I NEVER TOLD HIM.

546
00:42:41,533 --> 00:42:43,767
YOU WERE CLOSE.

547
00:42:46,001 --> 00:42:48,834
 <i>THAT IS FATOU,</i>
 <i>MY MOTHER.</i>

548
00:42:50,368 --> 00:42:54,301
AFTER MY FATHER LEFT,
IBOU BECAME OUR PRINCE.

549
00:42:54,301 --> 00:42:58,134
HE COULD DO NO WRONG.

550
00:42:58,134 --> 00:43:02,334
SHE SAVE FOR HIM TO
GO TO U.S. FOR A BETTER LIFE.

551
00:43:02,334 --> 00:43:04,867
IT IS ALL SHE THOUGHT ABOUT.

552
00:43:04,867 --> 00:43:09,434
AFTER HE LEFT, SHE WAS
FEELING TERRIBLE GRIEF,

553
00:43:09,434 --> 00:43:13,267
AND THEN THERE
WAS NOTHING LEFT.

554
00:43:13,267 --> 00:43:16,934
I CAN COUNT THE NUMBER
OF TIMES I WAS KISSED.

555
00:43:16,934 --> 00:43:21,567
ONCE WHEN I TURNED NINE,
AND THE OTHER WHEN I TURNED 10.

556
00:43:21,567 --> 00:43:25,334
I FELT A SPOT
ON MY CHEEK FOR DAYS,
AND IT MADE ME SAD,

557
00:43:25,334 --> 00:43:27,368
TRAGICALLY SAD.

558
00:43:27,368 --> 00:43:30,700
MMM. I WAS A VERY TRAGIC
LITTLE GIRL

559
00:43:30,700 --> 00:43:33,167
WALKING AROUND
WITH MY UNKISSED FACE.

560
00:43:42,468 --> 00:43:45,500
 <i>( dog barking )</i>

561
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:53,967
 <i>( pan sizzling )</i>

562
00:44:01,301 --> 00:44:03,633
EXCUSE ME.

563
00:44:03,633 --> 00:44:06,700
CAN YOU DRIVE ME, PLEASE,

564
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:09,667
TO THE HOSPITAL?

565
00:44:23,667 --> 00:44:25,900
 <i>( pager buzzes )</i>

566
00:44:25,900 --> 00:44:28,101
JESUS.

567
00:44:35,401 --> 00:44:37,334
( buzzing )

568
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:41,934
I HEARD YOU 
THE FIRST TIME.

569
00:44:41,934 --> 00:44:44,101
AND YOU FIGURE
WHAT'S THE HURRY, RIGHT?

570
00:44:44,101 --> 00:44:46,700
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY BE THE HURRY
IN AN INTENSIVE CARE UNIT?

571
00:44:46,700 --> 00:44:48,867
Man:
 <i>HOW CAN I HELP YOU?</i>

572
00:44:48,867 --> 00:44:51,101
Ben: <i>HOW LONG HAS</i>
 <i>IT BEEN SINCE YOU'VE</i>
 <i>CHANGED HIS SHEETS?</i>

573
00:44:51,101 --> 00:44:54,001
WHAT DO YOU FIGURE,
"SKIP THE VEGETABLE"?
IS THAT IT?

574
00:44:54,001 --> 00:44:56,301
Man: <i>I'LL--</i>
 <i>I'LL GET NEW BEDDING.</i>

575
00:44:56,301 --> 00:44:58,734
OH, THANKS.
TERRIFIC.

576
00:45:02,967 --> 00:45:06,533
I'M GETTING A SANDWICH.
DO YOU WANT ANYTHING?

577
00:45:06,533 --> 00:45:09,468
 <i>OH, NO--</i>
 <i>NO THANK YOU.</i>

578
00:45:09,468 --> 00:45:12,533
BEN?

579
00:45:12,533 --> 00:45:16,468
- I, UH--
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

580
00:45:40,234 --> 00:45:42,401
 <i>( objects scraping )</i>

581
00:45:53,900 --> 00:45:57,900
- ( speaks Wolof )
- YEAH, I KNOW.

582
00:45:57,900 --> 00:45:59,900
"THOUGHTS ARE THINGS."

583
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:03,101
 <i>ARE YOU ONE</i>
 <i>OF THOSE THINGS?</i>

584
00:46:03,101 --> 00:46:06,067
IS THAT WHY
YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS?

585
00:46:06,067 --> 00:46:08,201
IT'S ALL ABOUT
EXPECTATIONS. 

586
00:46:08,201 --> 00:46:10,201
SHE NEVER TOLD YOU
TO BACK OFF.

587
00:46:10,201 --> 00:46:12,434
IT WAS PRETTY OBVIOUS.

588
00:46:12,434 --> 00:46:14,900
HOW MUCH OF YOUR LIFE
IS YOUR FAULT

589
00:46:14,900 --> 00:46:17,034
AND HOW MUCH
IS THE WORLD'S?

590
00:46:17,034 --> 00:46:20,734
THAT IS YOUR
BIG QUESTION.

591
00:46:20,734 --> 00:46:22,600
YOU HAVE NO CAREER,

592
00:46:22,600 --> 00:46:24,401
YOU'VE BEEN FIRED
FROM YOUR JOB,

593
00:46:24,401 --> 00:46:26,734
YOUR OWN DAUGHTER
WON'T SPEAK TO YOU.

594
00:46:26,734 --> 00:46:30,134
BOTTOM LINE-- YOU CAN'T
EVEN EARN A LIVING.

595
00:46:30,134 --> 00:46:34,234
THAT'S WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT
FOR YOU, ISN'T IT? MONEY.

596
00:46:34,234 --> 00:46:36,700
LET'S TAKE MONEY
OUT OF THE EQUATION.

597
00:46:36,700 --> 00:46:40,001
WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE IT
TO BE ALL ABOUT?

598
00:46:43,301 --> 00:46:45,067
HEY, THERE HE IS.

599
00:46:45,067 --> 00:46:47,134
HEY, I'M GLAD YOU CAME.
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

600
00:46:47,134 --> 00:46:48,600
COME OVER HERE.

601
00:46:48,600 --> 00:46:52,234
SOMEBODY'S BIRTHDAY?

602
00:46:52,234 --> 00:46:54,667
CASSIE GOT
A GIG ON A SHOW.

603
00:46:57,867 --> 00:47:02,434
SO I FOUND THAT WHILE
I WAS GOING THROUGH
MY KIDS' OLD C.D.s.

604
00:47:06,001 --> 00:47:09,334
( laughs )
YOU'RE OUTTED, BRO.

605
00:47:09,334 --> 00:47:11,567
I-- I GOOGLED YOU.

606
00:47:11,567 --> 00:47:14,401
YOU WERE THE THIRD-BIGGEST
KIDDIE SINGER IN THE COUNTRY.

607
00:47:14,401 --> 00:47:17,234
YOU PLAYED
THE PASADENA CIVIC CENTER.

608
00:47:17,234 --> 00:47:19,167
GOD, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED,

609
00:47:19,167 --> 00:47:22,567
BUT WE'VE GOT TO GET YOU BACK
ON THAT KIDDIE GRAVY TRAIN.

610
00:47:22,567 --> 00:47:24,734
ALL RIGHT,
I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

611
00:47:24,734 --> 00:47:27,767
"WHY ME?"
WELL, I'M GONNA TELL YOU.

612
00:47:27,767 --> 00:47:30,401
UH, BECAUSE...

613
00:47:30,401 --> 00:47:33,434
I HAVE NO TALENT. NONE.

614
00:47:33,434 --> 00:47:37,468
ZIP. I USED TO COPY
OTHER KIDS' DRAWINGS
IN ART CLASS.

615
00:47:37,468 --> 00:47:40,267
I'M NOT KIDDING--
I CHEATED IN ART.

616
00:47:40,267 --> 00:47:44,334
SO THIS IS
AN EGO-FREE ZONE.

617
00:47:44,334 --> 00:47:46,267
WHEN DID YOU FIND OUT
ABOUT THIS?

618
00:47:46,267 --> 00:47:48,034
WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE?

619
00:47:48,034 --> 00:47:52,434
IF I WANTED A PARASITE,
I'D EAT RAW PORK.

620
00:47:54,201 --> 00:47:56,434
WHAT?WAIT.

621
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:07,934
YOU'RE BEATING YOUR HANDS
AGAINST A BOULDER.

622
00:48:13,533 --> 00:48:16,500
( ringing )

623
00:48:16,500 --> 00:48:18,368
HEY.

624
00:48:18,368 --> 00:48:21,334
- WHERE'S SANDRA?
- SHE'S AT HER FRIEND'S HOUSE.

625
00:48:21,334 --> 00:48:23,234
THEY'RE DOING
A BOOK REPORT TOGETHER.

626
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:25,067
I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE CALLED YOU.

627
00:48:32,900 --> 00:48:35,001
 <i>( door closes )</i>

628
00:48:46,934 --> 00:48:49,267
 <i>( doorbell rings )</i>

629
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:52,667
I WANT TO TALK TO HER.

630
00:48:52,667 --> 00:48:55,600
SHE'S AT
HER FRIEND'S HOUSE.

631
00:48:55,600 --> 00:48:56,834
BEN.

632
00:48:56,834 --> 00:48:58,600
- SANDRA?
- <i>BEN.</i>

633
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:00,167
- SANDRA!
- IS THERE A PROBLEM?

634
00:49:00,167 --> 00:49:01,767
NO, EVAN, I CAN
HANDLE THIS.

635
00:49:01,767 --> 00:49:03,667
- LET ME HANDLE IT, OKAY?
- YEAH. OKAY, EVAN?

636
00:49:03,667 --> 00:49:05,700
GO BACK TO THE DEN
WITH YOUR TOOLBOX.

637
00:49:05,700 --> 00:49:06,934
- <i>I'VE GOT IT.</i>
- SANDRA?

638
00:49:06,934 --> 00:49:08,567
THAT WASN'T VERY NICE.

639
00:49:08,567 --> 00:49:12,401
WELL, I THINK THE DIRECTOR
OF ACQUISITIVENESS CAN TAKE IT.

640
00:49:12,401 --> 00:49:14,468
DIRECTOR OF ACQUISITIONS.

641
00:49:14,468 --> 00:49:17,800
DIRECTOR OF ACQUISITIONS,
VICE PRESIDENT OF GREED--
WHATEVER.

642
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:21,034
- YOU KNOW WHAT HE IS.
- <i>BEN, GET OUT OF THE HOUSE</i>

643
00:49:21,034 --> 00:49:24,800
- <i>OR I AM CALLING THE POLICE.</i>
- I HAVE A RIGHT TO
SEE MY DAUGHTER.

644
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:27,368
YOU CAN'T KEEP HER LOCKED UP
HERE LIKE A PRISONER.

645
00:49:27,368 --> 00:49:29,234
LIKE A PRISONER?

646
00:49:29,234 --> 00:49:33,734
BEN, SHE IS THE ONE
WHO DOESN'T WANT TO SEE YOU.

647
00:49:33,734 --> 00:49:37,134
 <i>YOU-- YOU WANT</i>
 <i>TO KNOW WHY?</i>

648
00:49:37,134 --> 00:49:39,934
BECAUSE YOU
MAKE HER FEEL BAD.

649
00:49:39,934 --> 00:49:42,900
YOU KNOW, YOU POISON
THE AIR AROUND HER

650
00:49:42,900 --> 00:49:46,667
WITH ALL OF YOUR COMPLAINING.
AND HAVE YOU EVER EVER

651
00:49:46,667 --> 00:49:50,234
ASKED HER ONE QUESTION
ABOUT HERSELF?

652
00:49:51,734 --> 00:49:54,500
I MEAN,
YOU CAN'T EVEN SEE

653
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:57,067
THAT YOUR OWN DAUGHTER
IS HURTING.

654
00:49:57,067 --> 00:49:59,600
I MEAN, SHE DOESN'T
HAVE ANY FRIENDS.

655
00:49:59,600 --> 00:50:01,633
SHE'S CONFUSED.

656
00:50:01,633 --> 00:50:04,334
 <i>( suitcase rolling )</i>

657
00:50:07,401 --> 00:50:09,767
YOU COMING?

658
00:50:09,767 --> 00:50:13,900
SO DO YOU WANT TO GO
TO McRORY'S?

659
00:50:13,900 --> 00:50:16,767
NO, LET'S GO ICE SKATING.

660
00:50:16,767 --> 00:50:19,967
DAD, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO SKATE.

661
00:50:19,967 --> 00:50:22,301
WELL, MAYBE IT'S TIME
YOU LEARNED.

662
00:50:25,001 --> 00:50:28,267
DAD, I THINK
THE NEEDLE'S ON EMPTY.

663
00:50:28,267 --> 00:50:32,267
OH.THAT MEANS
THERE'S A HALF GALLON
LEFT IN THE TANK.

664
00:50:32,267 --> 00:50:35,334
THEY JUST DO THAT
SO YOU'LL BUY MORE
THAN YOU NEED.

665
00:50:35,334 --> 00:50:37,667
IT'S A CONSPIRACY BETWEEN
THE CAR COMPANIES

666
00:50:37,667 --> 00:50:39,600
AND THE OIL COMPANIES.

667
00:50:43,700 --> 00:50:47,134
WHAT KIND OF NEIGHBORHOOD
DOESN'T HAVE A GAS STATION?

668
00:50:47,134 --> 00:50:50,468
RESIDENTIAL ONES,
I GUESS.

669
00:50:53,034 --> 00:50:55,234
I'M SORRY.

670
00:50:55,234 --> 00:50:59,134
I REALLY WANTED YOU TO
HAVE A GOOD TIME TONIGHT.

671
00:50:59,134 --> 00:51:01,201
IT'S OKAY, DAD.

672
00:51:01,201 --> 00:51:04,301
IT'S AN ADVENTURE...

673
00:51:04,301 --> 00:51:05,934
SORT OF.

674
00:51:08,967 --> 00:51:11,401
( air pump humming )

675
00:51:11,401 --> 00:51:12,900
GOD DAMN IT.

676
00:51:12,900 --> 00:51:16,067
( humming )

677
00:51:26,167 --> 00:51:29,034
OKAY, NOW MOVE
THE POT SIDEWAYS.

678
00:51:29,034 --> 00:51:32,201
YES, AND THEN 
THE OTHER SIDE.

679
00:51:32,201 --> 00:51:35,001
YES, LIKE THAT.
MMM.

680
00:51:39,834 --> 00:51:42,600
WHAT DO YOU DO IN DAKAR?

681
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:47,067
I, UH--
I WORK IN HOTEL.

682
00:51:47,067 --> 00:51:51,867
I DON'T MEAN TO BE
ETHNOCENTRIC OR ANYTHING,

683
00:51:51,867 --> 00:51:54,867
 <i>BUT DO YOU GET PAID</i>
 <i>BELOW-SUBSISTENCE WAGES,</i>

684
00:51:54,867 --> 00:51:57,667
LIKE $5 A DAY
OR ANYTHING?

685
00:51:57,667 --> 00:52:00,134
MY LIFE IS ONE
OF MISERY AND PAIN.

686
00:52:00,134 --> 00:52:02,101
DOES THAT MAKE YOU
FEEL BETTER?

687
00:52:02,101 --> 00:52:04,434
- I'M SORRY.
- ( laughs )

688
00:52:04,434 --> 00:52:07,633
I WAS BEING SHALLOW
AND STUPID.

689
00:52:07,633 --> 00:52:10,468
I WAS BEING A TOTAL
ASSHOLE AMERICAN.

690
00:52:10,468 --> 00:52:12,533
MY COUNTRY IS VERY
DIFFERENT FROM YOURS,

691
00:52:12,533 --> 00:52:14,867
BUT WE HAVE FUN TOO.

692
00:52:14,867 --> 00:52:17,533
THERE ARE CLUBS,
WE HAVE MUSIC.

693
00:52:17,533 --> 00:52:19,134
WE LISTEN
TO A LOT OF MUSIC.

694
00:52:19,134 --> 00:52:21,301
WE SENEGALESE
LOVE TO DANCE.

695
00:52:23,934 --> 00:52:26,401
 <i>( folk music playing )</i>

696
00:52:26,401 --> 00:52:28,301
GO ON,
TRY IT.

697
00:52:28,301 --> 00:52:30,234
I'M SO INEPT
AT DANCING.

698
00:52:30,234 --> 00:52:32,301
THERE OUGHT TO BE
A SPECIAL RING IN HELL

699
00:52:32,301 --> 00:52:34,900
FOR THE GUY WHO INVENTED
THE AIR MATTRESS.

700
00:52:34,900 --> 00:52:37,600
YOU ARE BEING ETHNOCENTRIC.
COME ON.

701
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:40,567
I'M A TOTAL KLUTZ!

702
00:52:40,567 --> 00:52:42,500
TRY IT.

703
00:52:48,434 --> 00:52:50,867
Sandra:
 <i>I KNOW.</i>
 <i>IT'S GENETIC.</i>

704
00:52:52,734 --> 00:52:55,401
YOU ARE MAKING HER
SELF-CONSCIOUS.

705
00:52:55,401 --> 00:52:57,934
YOU WANT ME TO LEAVE?

706
00:53:03,600 --> 00:53:06,101
OKAY.

707
00:53:06,101 --> 00:53:08,167
OKAY, YES!

708
00:53:08,167 --> 00:53:09,468
YES!

709
00:53:09,468 --> 00:53:11,600
( laughs )

710
00:53:20,934 --> 00:53:23,067
 <i>( drums playing )</i>

711
00:54:26,667 --> 00:54:27,867
WOW!

712
00:54:27,867 --> 00:54:30,533
- <i>WOW.</i>
- AHH!

713
00:54:33,900 --> 00:54:36,101
YOU WORE HER OUT.

714
00:54:37,201 --> 00:54:39,468
HERE.

715
00:56:00,267 --> 00:56:02,201
THAT WAS FUN.

716
00:56:08,633 --> 00:56:10,234
BYE.

717
00:56:34,301 --> 00:56:37,368
Khadi:
 <i>THIS IS MISTAKE.</i>

718
00:56:37,368 --> 00:56:40,401
 <i>I DID NOT WANT</i>
 <i>TO DO THIS AGAIN.</i>

719
00:56:40,401 --> 00:56:42,667
Ben:
 <i>WHY?</i>

720
00:56:42,667 --> 00:56:46,834
Khadi:
 <i>I DO NOT WANT TO BE--</i>

721
00:56:46,834 --> 00:56:50,234
HOW YOU SAY?
--YOUR MISTRESS.

722
00:56:50,234 --> 00:56:52,001
MY MISTRESS?

723
00:56:52,001 --> 00:56:54,234
THERE IS NO TIME
FOR ANYTHING ELSE.

724
00:56:54,234 --> 00:56:56,234
I HAVE TWO WEEKS LEFT
ON MY VISA.

725
00:56:56,234 --> 00:56:59,368
TO STAY HERE,
I WOULD NEED GREEN CARD.

726
00:56:59,368 --> 00:57:03,934
BUT YOU-- WE DO NOT
KNOW EACH OTHER ENOUGH.

727
00:57:03,934 --> 00:57:07,101
IT IS IMPOSSIBLE.

728
00:57:07,101 --> 00:57:09,167
WE ARE LIKE
DIFFERENT SPECIES.

729
00:57:09,167 --> 00:57:12,567
WE ARE LIKE LION AND
HIPPO TRYING TO MATE.

730
00:57:12,567 --> 00:57:15,434
WHICH ONE IS THE HIPPO?

731
00:57:15,434 --> 00:57:17,034
YOU.

732
00:57:17,034 --> 00:57:19,867
DO I LOOK
LIKE A HIPPO?

733
00:57:19,867 --> 00:57:23,900
SO YOU DON'T THINK THERE'S
ANY HOPE FOR US AT ALL?

734
00:57:23,900 --> 00:57:25,434
NONE...

735
00:57:25,434 --> 00:57:27,633
- MMM?
- ...WHATSOEVER.

736
00:57:28,934 --> 00:57:31,167
I AM BAD.

737
00:57:31,167 --> 00:57:35,267
I SEE SOMETHING I LIKE
AND I MUST HAVE IT.

738
00:57:35,267 --> 00:57:37,267
I AM GREEDY.

739
00:57:37,267 --> 00:57:39,301
THERE'S NOTHING BAD
ABOUT YOU.

740
00:57:39,301 --> 00:57:42,967
YOU DO NOT KNOW
EVERY PART OF ME.

741
00:57:42,967 --> 00:57:45,800
WHAT PART DON'T I KNOW?

742
00:57:47,434 --> 00:57:49,567
RIGHT HERE...

743
00:57:51,600 --> 00:57:53,201
AND HERE...

744
00:57:55,533 --> 00:57:58,101
AND HERE.

745
00:57:58,101 --> 00:58:00,234
I KNOW IT A LITTLE.

746
00:58:00,234 --> 00:58:03,034
GET TO KNOW IT BETTER.

747
00:58:19,001 --> 00:58:22,500
HOW COME
YOU QUIT SINGING
FOR CHILDREN, BEN?

748
00:58:22,500 --> 00:58:24,600
THE RECORD COMPANY SAID

749
00:58:24,600 --> 00:58:27,667
THAT THEY'D PRODUCE
AN ACOUSTIC SOLO ALBUM

750
00:58:27,667 --> 00:58:30,167
IF I WENT ON
A NATIONAL CHILDREN'S TOUR.

751
00:58:30,167 --> 00:58:33,001
AND THE RECORD COMPANY
WENT BACK ON ITS WORD?

752
00:58:33,001 --> 00:58:35,667
 <i>NO, THEY PRODUCED IT,</i>
 <i>BUT THEY DUMPED IT.</i>

753
00:58:35,667 --> 00:58:37,967
THEY DIDN'T PROMOTE IT.

754
00:58:37,967 --> 00:58:40,967
THEY DIDN'T ADVERTISE.

755
00:58:40,967 --> 00:58:43,468
THEY SAID IT
WASN'T ACCESSIBLE.

756
00:58:43,468 --> 00:58:46,167
BOTTOM LINE.

757
00:58:46,167 --> 00:58:48,401
YEAH.
BOTTOM LINE.

758
00:58:52,368 --> 00:58:55,134
YOU HAVE C.D.?

759
00:58:55,134 --> 00:58:58,967
THE ONE THE RECORD COMPANY
DID NOT WANT TO PROMOTE?

760
00:58:58,967 --> 00:59:00,967
YOU DON'T WANT
TO HEAR THAT.

761
00:59:00,967 --> 00:59:02,967
I WOULD LIKE TO HEAR IT.

762
00:59:18,533 --> 00:59:21,834
YOU'RE PROBABLY
ONE OF 10 PEOPLE 
WHO'S HEARD THIS.

763
00:59:24,867 --> 00:59:29,633
 <i>( guitar music playing )</i>

764
00:59:42,201 --> 00:59:44,900
I SEE WHY
YOU GOT ANGRY.

765
00:59:48,167 --> 00:59:52,001
IT IS MAYBE TOO QUIET
FOR THE WORLD.

766
01:00:07,167 --> 01:00:09,301
 <i>( fly buzzing )</i>

767
01:00:17,600 --> 01:00:19,567
 <i>( buzzing stops )</i>

768
01:00:22,600 --> 01:00:25,101
Bailiff: 
 <i>ALL RISE.</i>

769
01:00:25,101 --> 01:00:27,134
Judge:
 <i>BE SEATED.</i>

770
01:00:31,067 --> 01:00:34,468
YOU GUYS MULTIPLY
LIKE AMOEBAS.

771
01:00:34,468 --> 01:00:37,633
HOW COULD THE TOW-TRUCK
DRIVER KNOW

772
01:00:37,633 --> 01:00:40,134
THAT TOWING MR. SINGER'S CAR
WOULD LEAD TO MR. NIDIA'S-- 

773
01:00:40,134 --> 01:00:41,900
N'DIYAE.

774
01:00:41,900 --> 01:00:45,468
--MR. N'DIYAE GOING INTO
A DIABETIC COMA?

775
01:00:45,468 --> 01:00:47,301
I MEAN, IS HE A DOCTOR?

776
01:00:47,301 --> 01:00:49,567
IS HE A TRAINED NURSE?

777
01:00:49,567 --> 01:00:53,001
THE FACT IS, BEN SINGER
WAS PARKED ILLEGALLY

778
01:00:53,001 --> 01:00:56,101
 <i>AND THE TOW-TRUCK DRIVER</i>
 <i>SIMPLY DID HIS JOB.</i>

779
01:00:56,101 --> 01:00:59,867
YOUR HONOR,
THIS IS A NO-BRAINER.

780
01:01:03,101 --> 01:01:06,234
I KNOW I'M JUST A--
A JOKE TO YOU,

781
01:01:06,234 --> 01:01:09,567
AND YOU ONLY DECIDED TO
HEAR MY CASE BECAUSE
YOU WERE AMUSED.

782
01:01:09,567 --> 01:01:13,734
SOME CRACKPOT ACTING
AS HIS OWN ATTORNEY 

783
01:01:13,734 --> 01:01:16,468
ACCUSING THE CITY
OF DEPRAVED INDIFFERENCE.

784
01:01:16,468 --> 01:01:20,500
YOU KNOW WHAT
THE MOST CROWDED ROOM IS
IN THE GETTY MUSEUM?

785
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:23,767
IT'S THE ROOM WITH
VAN GOGH'S "IRISES."

786
01:01:23,767 --> 01:01:28,633
WHY? BECAUSE SOMEONE BOUGHT 
THE PAINTING FOR $54 MILLION.

787
01:01:28,633 --> 01:01:32,867
THERE'S A REVERENTIAL SILENCE
IN THE IRIS ROOM.

788
01:01:32,867 --> 01:01:34,934
MR. AND MRS. MUSEUM-GOER

789
01:01:34,934 --> 01:01:39,334
MIGHT AS WELL BE LOOKING 
AT A FRAMED PILE OF CASH.

790
01:01:39,334 --> 01:01:42,800
NEWSPAPERS PUBLISH
MOVIE GROSSES.

791
01:01:42,800 --> 01:01:45,201
IF A MOVIE EARNS OVER
$100 MILLION,

792
01:01:45,201 --> 01:01:47,034
WE ASSUME
IT MUST BE GOOD.

793
01:01:47,034 --> 01:01:50,267
THERE'S NO GOD.
THERE'S NO BEAUTY.

794
01:01:50,267 --> 01:01:54,533
IF A PAINTING OR A C.D.
DOESN'T SELL, THROW IT OUT.

795
01:01:54,533 --> 01:01:58,834
THE 910 FREEWAY HAS
A VERY SHARP TURN

796
01:01:58,834 --> 01:02:01,834
 <i>AS IT WINDS INTO THE VALLEY</i>
 <i>FROM THE HILLS,</i>

797
01:02:01,834 --> 01:02:06,334
AND EVERY YEAR
FOUR OR FIVE MOTORISTS
ARE KILLED ON THIS SPOT.

798
01:02:06,334 --> 01:02:09,633
THE CITY CONDUCTED
A COST-AND-EFFECT STUDY,

799
01:02:09,633 --> 01:02:12,900
AND THE STUDY CONCLUDED
THAT THE COST IN TERMS 
OF HUMAN LIFE

800
01:02:12,900 --> 01:02:17,001
WAS NOT EQUAL TO THE COST 
OF REBUILDING THE HIGHWAY.

801
01:02:17,001 --> 01:02:20,401
AND SO THIS DEADLY SPOT
ON THE HIGHWAY REMAINS,

802
01:02:20,401 --> 01:02:23,500
AND IN FIVE YEARS
20 MORE PEOPLE WILL DIE.

803
01:02:23,500 --> 01:02:26,234
WELL, IF THIS ISN'T
DEPRAVED INDIFFERENCE,

804
01:02:26,234 --> 01:02:28,267
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IS.

805
01:02:31,034 --> 01:02:35,267
IBOU N'DIYAE CAME HERE
FROM SENEGAL.

806
01:02:35,267 --> 01:02:39,834
HE WORKED AS A GUARD
AT AN OUTLET STORE IN CARSON.

807
01:02:39,834 --> 01:02:43,034
HE'S A GREAT CHESS PLAYER.
HE'S MY FRIEND...

808
01:02:44,567 --> 01:02:49,034
AND HE WAS THROWN AWAY.

809
01:02:49,034 --> 01:02:51,934
WELL, WHAT KIND
OF A WORLD DO WE LIVE IN
THAT HIS LIFE

810
01:02:51,934 --> 01:02:55,767
IS WORTH LESS THAN
THIS NOBODY'S ABILITY
TO GET QUICKLY

811
01:02:55,767 --> 01:02:57,401
 <i>INTO A PARKING SPACE</i>

812
01:02:57,401 --> 01:02:59,767
OR THE CITY IMPOUND'S
NEED FOR REVENUE,

813
01:02:59,767 --> 01:03:02,533
SO THAT EACH ONE
OF THESE AMOEBAS

814
01:03:02,533 --> 01:03:06,167
CAN HAVE
A BEACH HOUSE IN MIAMI?

815
01:03:06,167 --> 01:03:09,633
IS THAT REALLY THE KIND OF
WORLD WE WANT TO LIVE IN? 

816
01:03:09,633 --> 01:03:12,700
Bailiff:
 <i>ALL RISE.</i>

817
01:03:16,633 --> 01:03:20,700
MY SYMPATHY IS
WITH MR. N'DIYAE

818
01:03:20,700 --> 01:03:23,034
AND I WISH HIM
A SPEEDY RECOVERY.

819
01:03:23,034 --> 01:03:24,600
HOWEVER,

820
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:27,734
A TOW-TRUCK DRIVER IS NOT

821
01:03:27,734 --> 01:03:30,567
A TRAINED MEDICAL
DIAGNOSTICIAN

822
01:03:30,567 --> 01:03:34,301
 <i>AND SHOULD NOT BE EXPECTED</i>
 <i>TO BEHAVE LIKE ONE.</i>

823
01:03:34,301 --> 01:03:36,201
BOTTOM LINE--

824
01:03:36,201 --> 01:03:40,301
YOU WERE PARKED
IN THE WRONG PLACE
AT THE WRONG TIME.

825
01:03:40,301 --> 01:03:44,600
 <i>I RULE IN FAVOR</i>
 <i>OF THE DEFENSE.</i>

826
01:03:44,600 --> 01:03:47,567
I HOPE THE WESTERN WORLD
SURVIVES.

827
01:03:57,468 --> 01:04:00,434
CAN'T WE JUST AGREE
TO DISAGREE?

828
01:04:00,434 --> 01:04:03,101
FUCK YOU.

829
01:04:47,667 --> 01:04:51,700
Khadi:
 <i>I THINK WE MADE</i>
 <i>A CONNECTION, YES.</i>

830
01:04:51,700 --> 01:04:53,800
Ibou:
 <i>DO YOU THINK</i>
 <i>HE WILL MARRY YOU?</i>

831
01:04:53,800 --> 01:04:55,900
 <i>YES, I THINK</i>
 <i>HE WILL MARRY ME.</i>

832
01:04:55,900 --> 01:04:57,301
GET GREEN CARD THEN.

833
01:04:59,800 --> 01:05:03,067
YOU GET GREEN CARD,
THERE IS MORE OPPORTUNITY
FOR YOU.

834
01:05:03,067 --> 01:05:05,034
AH, <i>OUI.</i>
MM-HMM.

835
01:05:05,034 --> 01:05:06,800
THAT IS ALL GOOD, KHADI.

836
01:05:06,800 --> 01:05:10,134
ARE YOU FEELING OKAY?
HMM?

837
01:05:10,134 --> 01:05:12,633
OKAY, SIR, WE'RE GONNA GET YOU
UP IN THE WHEELCHAIR NOW.

838
01:05:12,633 --> 01:05:15,368
- ( Khadi speaks Wolof )
- <i>OUI.</i>

839
01:05:15,368 --> 01:05:17,500
 <i>HERE YOU GO.</i>

840
01:05:38,334 --> 01:05:40,667
( sighs )

841
01:06:12,867 --> 01:06:16,301
DID YOU REALLY THINK
THAT YOU'D GET AWAY WITH IT?

842
01:06:16,301 --> 01:06:18,867
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, BEN?

843
01:06:18,867 --> 01:06:21,600
DID YOU REALLY THINK
THAT I WAS GONNA WALK
DOWN THE AISLE WITH YOU

844
01:06:21,600 --> 01:06:23,633
WHILE YOU WERE PICKING
MY FUCKING POCKET?

845
01:06:23,633 --> 01:06:26,667
JESUS, YOU'RE
REALLY SOMETHING

846
01:06:26,667 --> 01:06:28,767
WITH YOUR BULLSHIT
AFRICAN DANCING

847
01:06:28,767 --> 01:06:31,401
AND YOUR "I'M GONNA
COOK YOU A WOLOF MEAL."

848
01:06:31,401 --> 01:06:33,934
THE WHOLE TIME,
YOU'RE NOTHING 
BUT A CON ARTIST.

849
01:06:33,934 --> 01:06:37,567
I-- I DO NOT KNOW WHY YOU
ARE SAYING THESE THINGS.

850
01:06:37,567 --> 01:06:39,301
DON'T GIVE ME
THAT INNOCENCE CRAP.

851
01:06:39,301 --> 01:06:42,234
THE WHOLE TIME
YOU'VE BEEN PLAYING ME.

852
01:06:42,234 --> 01:06:45,500
YOU'VE BEEN PROSTITUTING
YOURSELF FOR AN AMERICAN
CITIZENSHIP.

853
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:52,267
REMEMBER THAT SLAP.

854
01:06:52,267 --> 01:06:55,267
IT'S THE LAST TIME
WE TOUCH.

855
01:07:25,034 --> 01:07:26,800
 <i>( knock on door )</i>

856
01:07:26,800 --> 01:07:29,001
EH!
( speaks Wolof )

857
01:07:29,001 --> 01:07:31,368
( repeats phrase )

858
01:07:36,368 --> 01:07:39,368
THE ANGRY MAN, HUH?

859
01:07:39,368 --> 01:07:42,700
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU
BACK IN THE LAND
OF THE LIVING.

860
01:07:42,700 --> 01:07:45,900
EH, MAYBE I GO BACK
INTO COMA, EH?

861
01:07:45,900 --> 01:07:47,633
( laughs )

862
01:07:50,001 --> 01:07:51,967
IS SHE HERE?

863
01:07:51,967 --> 01:07:54,867
KHADI WENT BACK
TO DAKAR.

864
01:07:54,867 --> 01:07:57,633
 <i>YOU KNOW, BEN,</i>

865
01:07:57,633 --> 01:08:00,867
SHE WAS NOT ONLY
AFTER YOUR GREEN CARD.

866
01:08:00,867 --> 01:08:05,067
 <i>IT IS POSSIBLE</i>
 <i>TO LOVE SOMEONE</i>

867
01:08:05,067 --> 01:08:07,934
AND TO ALSO WANT
SOMETHING FROM THEM.

868
01:08:07,934 --> 01:08:10,600
GAME THEORY.

869
01:08:41,934 --> 01:08:44,368
IDEALLY, WE'D KEEP YOU
A COUPLE MORE DAYS,

870
01:08:44,368 --> 01:08:46,867
BUT MEDICAID STOPS PAYING
ONCE YOUR VITALS ARE NORMAL.

871
01:08:46,867 --> 01:08:49,134
ANY PAIN, ANY DIZZINESS

872
01:08:49,134 --> 01:08:51,734
OR PAIN HERE,
YOU CALL, OKAY?

873
01:08:51,734 --> 01:08:53,301
OKAY, DOCTOR.

874
01:08:55,967 --> 01:08:58,800
WELL, IT'S ALL
ABOUT LIABILITY.

875
01:08:58,800 --> 01:09:01,434
THEY'LL RELEASE YOU WHEN
YOUR LIFE IS STILL IN DANGER,

876
01:09:01,434 --> 01:09:03,867
BUT YOU GOTTA BE
IN A WHEELCHAIR.

877
01:09:03,867 --> 01:09:06,934
YOU KNOW, HAS ANYONE
EVER TOLD YOU THAT

